history.text: What's up?
Hey! Did you like Batman v Superman?
People would hate my by saying this but yes because of Wonder Woman mainly lol.
How about you?
That's funny! I love Wonder Woman. I thought Ben Affleck was great and Amy Adams; I really like it
I know right?! I mean they could've done a better job only if Warner Bros would just leave it to Zack Snyder but youre right. Batfleck did not disappoint! haha

A critic did say "153 minutes of grown man whacking two dolls together, has the definition of 'movie' changed from 'motion picture story that a human wrote on purpose' to '700 only
tangentially related 12-second grey and red vignettes’?”
But I think that is too harsh, what do you think?
Pfft, these critics are always harsh to these DC movies.
Lol! What would rate it out of ten? (Rotten tomatoes gave 4.9/10)
Haha it should be at least 6 to me.
*would you rate it out of ten
7 if only Jesse Eisenberg was not a miscast.
I mean I like him as an actor but I know Lex Luthor when I see one lol
Did you see him in the last part of Justice League? They shouldve gone with that version of Lex played by Jesse in the first place!

Interesting! One critic said ""As the film progresses, Lex degenerates into a gibbering mad man, some strange mix of
the Riddler and the Joker with a little bit of Mark Zuckerberg added for flair."
Sorry different movie haha;
I might agree to that haha.
lol! Do you think people just think of Jesse Eisenberg as only Mark Zuckerberg now? lol
I cant say for other people but to me I again I like him as an actor and Mark Zuckerberg aint human, hes a reptile! sshhh, ;)
That's so funny! Is that a David Ike reference?
You know it. :D
Remember the scene where Martha was saved by Batfleck?

One critic said, "As the film progresses, Lex degenerates into a gibbering mad man, some strange mix of
the Riddler and the Joker with a little bit of Mark Zuckerberg added for flair."
And Martha was like yeah, you look like a friend of my alien son, you have a cape you weirdo. Remember that? That shit was funny.
Do you think that critic has a point? Did you notice any sinister symbolism or even illuminati symbols?! LOL
I actually don't remember that part, but I did think the movie was funny
Youre being weird, what illuminati symbols!?
I am!
I mean just do you think it was sinster?
s
Sinster?
Do you think it was fair for the critic to compare it to Heath Ledger's former performance?
Did you get that kind of tone?
It is never fair!
Heath Ledger is a legend for that role!
lol true!
Even Anne Hathaway!
For Catwoman!
Haters said they were miscasts.
Lex Luthor was the only miscast!
Once critic said “better than Man of Steel but below the high bar set by Nolan's Dark Knight”

uid2response.feedback: People hate what they don't understand.
